@node intro "Introduction"

@{u}Introduction@{uu}

Basically it's a picture only version of MultiView! :)  However, Sview works by calling ScrollRaster() and only blitting the extra bits of the image each time you scroll - unlike multiview which redraws the entire window - to get silky smooth scrolling (better than anything I've seen elsewhere).

It's good for people with graphics cards.  If you have no gfx card; look at FastView or ViewTek.  However unlike CyberWindow (which is crap anyway) SView works under AGA as well.

If, however, like me you have both pot loads of RAM and a Cgfx card this is MUCH faster than CyberWindow or Multiview.  Like MView Sview works with the system datatypes but supports 24bit images as well (doesn't do anything nasty when blitting...)

SpeedyView uses the datatypes system and can utilise 24-bit datatypes where found under Picasso96 and Cybergraphics as well as standard images under AGA.

@endnode

@node req "Requirements"

@{u}Requirements@{uu}

Any Amiga running OS 2.1 or above that uses datatypes.  Best when run with V43 picture.datatype using a GFX board.

Lots of RAM is handy when viewing big images.

@endnode

@node cli "CLI Usage"

@{u}CLI Usage@{uu}

The following parameters are supported:

	SCREEN=screenname, e.g: SCREEN=Workbench

Public screen name for the window to open on.  This can be "TOP" which means sview opens on the top screen (handy for dir utils) but note that it won't Lock the screen if the screen is public which can be dangerous!

When using the TOP option sview can be made to open on non-public screens - but again this is dangerous.

	REFRESH=refreshmode. e.g: REFRESH=SMART or REFRESH=SIMPLE

Type of refresh mode for the window, under CV64 gfx boards using SIMPLE for speed, but most other environments use SMART.

	MESSAGE=yes|no, e.g: MESSAGE=YES or MESSAGE=NO

Display a loading message when decoding, defaults to YES.

Then just pass the filename of the image to view.

Simple!

@endnode

@node wb "Workbench Usage"

@{u}Workbench Usage@{uu}

SView may be used as the DEFAULT TOOL of a picture icon or can be launched by holding down shift clicking on the Sview icon then double-clicking on the image to view.

The following TOOLTYPES are implemented as options:

	PUBSCREEN=screenname

	TOPSCREEN=yes|no

	SMARTREFRESH=yes|no
	
	SIMPLEREFRESH=yes|no
	
	MESSAGE=yes|no
	
see @{" CLI Options " link cli} for details on these options


@endnode

@node history "History of changes"

@{u}History of changes@{uu}

@{b}Version 1.4@{ub}

Adjusted decode routine to use half the memory needed (keeping DTobj alive)
Added keyboard options; Esc + Cursor controls
Adjusted with of scroller again to make arrows aligned correctly
Added startup message + option to turn it off.

@{b}Version 1.3@{ub}

Fixed corruption bug with images not exactly divisible by 8
Increased widths of horizontal scoller
Added CLI and WB options to use SMART or SIMPLE refreshes
Added CLI and WB option to open on any public screen 
Added CLI and WB option to open on the top screen
Wrote this help file!

@endnode

